57/*
58 * State for a Deflate (de)compressor.
59 */
60struct deflate_state {
61 int seqno;
62 int w_size;
63 int unit;
64 int hdrlen;
65 int mru;
66 int debug;
67 z_stream strm;
68 struct compstat stats;
69};
70
71#define DEFLATE_OVHD 2 /* Deflate overhead/packet */
72
73static void *z_alloc __P((void *, u_int items, u_int size));
74static void z_free __P((void *, void *ptr, u_int nb));
75static void *z_decomp_alloc __P((u_char *options, int opt_len));
76static void z_decomp_free __P((void *state));
77static int z_decomp_init __P((void *state, u_char *options, int opt_len,
78 int unit, int hdrlen, int mru, int debug));
79static void z_incomp __P((void *state, PACKETPTR mi));
80static int z_decompress __P((void *state, PACKETPTR mi, PACKETPTR *mo));
81static void z_decomp_reset __P((void *state));
82static void z_comp_stats __P((void *state, struct compstat *stats));

85 * Procedures exported to if_ppp.c.

99 z_decompress, /* decompress */
100 z_incomp, /* incomp */
101 z_comp_stats, /* decomp_stat */
102};

104/*
105 * Space allocation and freeing routines for use by zlib routines.
106 */
107static void *
108z_alloc(notused, items, size)
109 void *notused;
110 u_int items, size;
111{
112 return malloc(items * size);
113}
114
115static void
116z_free(notused, ptr, nbytes)
117 void *notused;
118 void *ptr;
119 u_int nbytes;
120{
121 free(ptr);
122}
123
124static void
125z_comp_stats(arg, stats)
126 void *arg;
127 struct compstat *stats;
128{
129 struct deflate_state *state = (struct deflate_state *) arg;
130 u_int out;
131
132 *stats = state->stats;
133 stats->ratio = stats->unc_bytes;
134 out = stats->comp_bytes + stats->unc_bytes;
135 if (stats->ratio <= 0x7ffffff)
136 stats->ratio <<= 8;
137 else
138 out >>= 8;
139 if (out != 0)
140 stats->ratio /= out;
141}
142
143/*
144 * Allocate space for a decompressor.
145 */
146static void *
147z_decomp_alloc(options, opt_len)
148 u_char *options;
149 int opt_len;
150{
151 struct deflate_state *state;
152 int w_size;
153
154 if (opt_len != CILEN_DEFLATE || options[0] != CI_DEFLATE
155 || options[1] != CILEN_DEFLATE
156 || DEFLATE_METHOD(options[2]) != DEFLATE_METHOD_VAL
157 || options[3] != DEFLATE_CHK_SEQUENCE)
158 return NULL;
159 w_size = DEFLATE_SIZE(options[2]);
160 if (w_size < DEFLATE_MIN_SIZE || w_size > DEFLATE_MAX_SIZE)
161 return NULL;
162
163 state = (struct deflate_state *) malloc(sizeof(*state));
164 if (state == NULL)
165 return NULL;
166
167 state->strm.next_out = NULL;
168 state->strm.zalloc = (alloc_func) z_alloc;
169 state->strm.zfree = (free_func) z_free;
170 if (inflateInit2(&state->strm, -w_size) != Z_OK) {
171 free(state);
172 return NULL;
173 }
174
175 state->w_size = w_size;
176 memset(&state->stats, 0, sizeof(state->stats));
177 return (void *) state;
178}
179
180static void
181z_decomp_free(arg)
182 void *arg;
183{
184 struct deflate_state *state = (struct deflate_state *) arg;
185
186 inflateEnd(&state->strm);
187 free(state);
188}
189
190static int
191z_decomp_init(arg, options, opt_len, unit, hdrlen, mru, debug)
192 void *arg;
193 u_char *options;
194 int opt_len, unit, hdrlen, mru, debug;
195{
196 struct deflate_state *state = (struct deflate_state *) arg;
197
198 if (opt_len < CILEN_DEFLATE || options[0] != CI_DEFLATE
199 || options[1] != CILEN_DEFLATE
200 || DEFLATE_METHOD(options[2]) != DEFLATE_METHOD_VAL
201 || DEFLATE_SIZE(options[2]) != state->w_size
202 || options[3] != DEFLATE_CHK_SEQUENCE)
203 return 0;
204
205 state->seqno = 0;
206 state->unit = unit;
207 state->hdrlen = hdrlen;
208 state->debug = debug;
209 state->mru = mru;
210
211 inflateReset(&state->strm);
212
213 return 1;
214}
215
216static void
217z_decomp_reset(arg)
218 void *arg;
219{
220 struct deflate_state *state = (struct deflate_state *) arg;
221
222 state->seqno = 0;
223 inflateReset(&state->strm);
224}

226/*
227 * Decompress a Deflate-compressed packet.
228 *
229 * Because of patent problems, we return DECOMP_ERROR for errors
230 * found by inspecting the input data and for system problems, but
231 * DECOMP_FATALERROR for any errors which could possibly be said to
232 * be being detected "after" decompression. For DECOMP_ERROR,
233 * we can issue a CCP reset-request; for DECOMP_FATALERROR, we may be
234 * infringing a patent of Motorola's if we do, so we take CCP down
235 * instead.
236 *
237 * Given that the frame has the correct sequence number and a good FCS,
238 * errors such as invalid codes in the input most likely indicate a
239 * bug, so we return DECOMP_FATALERROR for them in order to turn off
240 * compression, even though they are detected by inspecting the input.
241 */
242static int
243z_decompress(arg, mi, mo)
244 void *arg;
245 PACKETPTR mi;
246 PACKETPTR *mo;
247{
248 struct deflate_state *state = (struct deflate_state *) arg;
249 u_char *rptr, *wptr;
250 int rlen, olen;
251 int seq, r;
252
253 rptr = mi->buf;
254 if (*rptr == 0)
255 ++rptr;
256 ++rptr;
257
258 /* Check the sequence number. */
259 seq = (rptr[0] << 8) + rptr[1];
260 rptr += 2;
261 if (seq != state->seqno) {
262#if !DEFLATE_DEBUG
263 if (state->debug)
264#endif
265 printf("z_decompress%d: bad seq # %d, expected %d\n",
266 state->unit, seq, state->seqno);
267 return DECOMP_ERROR;
268 }
269 ++state->seqno;
270
271 /*
272 * Set up to call inflate.
273 */
274 wptr = (*mo)->buf;
275 state->strm.next_in = rptr;
276 state->strm.avail_in = mi->buf + mi->len - rptr;
277 rlen = state->strm.avail_in + PPP_HDRLEN + DEFLATE_OVHD;
278 state->strm.next_out = wptr;
279 state->strm.avail_out = state->mru + 2;
280
281 r = inflate(&state->strm, Z_PACKET_FLUSH);
282 if (r != Z_OK) {
283#if !DEFLATE_DEBUG
284 if (state->debug)
285#endif
286 printf("z_decompress%d: inflate returned %d (%s)\n",
287 state->unit, r, (state->strm.msg? state->strm.msg: ""));
288 return DECOMP_FATALERROR;
289 }
290 olen = state->mru + 2 - state->strm.avail_out;
291 (*mo)->len = olen;
292
293 if ((wptr[0] & 1) != 0)
294 ++olen; /* for suppressed protocol high byte */
295 olen += 2; /* for address, control */
296
297#if DEFLATE_DEBUG
298 if (olen > state->mru + PPP_HDRLEN)
299 printf("ppp_deflate%d: exceeded mru (%d > %d)\n",
300 state->unit, olen, state->mru + PPP_HDRLEN);
301#endif
302
303 state->stats.unc_bytes += olen;
304 state->stats.unc_packets++;
305 state->stats.comp_bytes += rlen;
306 state->stats.comp_packets++;
307
308 return DECOMP_OK;
309}
310
311/*
312 * Incompressible data has arrived - add it to the history.
313 */
314static void
315z_incomp(arg, mi)
316 void *arg;
317 PACKETPTR mi;
318{
319 struct deflate_state *state = (struct deflate_state *) arg;
320 u_char *rptr;
321 int rlen, proto, r;
322
323 /*
324 * Check that the protocol is one we handle.
325 */
326 rptr = mi->buf;
327 proto = rptr[0];
328 if ((proto & 1) == 0)
329 proto = (proto << 8) + rptr[1];
330 if (proto > 0x3fff || proto == 0xfd || proto == 0xfb)
331 return;
332
333 ++state->seqno;
334
335 if (rptr[0] == 0)
336 ++rptr;
337 rlen = mi->buf + mi->len - rptr;
338 state->strm.next_in = rptr;
339 state->strm.avail_in = rlen;
340 r = inflateIncomp(&state->strm);
341 if (r != Z_OK) {
342 /* gak! */
343#if !DEFLATE_DEBUG
344 if (state->debug)
345#endif
346 printf("z_incomp%d: inflateIncomp returned %d (%s)\n",
347 state->unit, r, (state->strm.msg? state->strm.msg: ""));
348 return;
349 }
350
351 /*
352 * Update stats.
353 */
354 if (proto <= 0xff)
355 ++rlen;
356 rlen += 2;
357 state->stats.inc_bytes += rlen;
358 state->stats.inc_packets++;
359 state->stats.unc_bytes += rlen;
360 state->stats.unc_packets++;
361}
